headline: Keysight (NYSE:KEYS) Posts Better-Than-Expected Sales In Q3, Stock Jumps 10.2%
summary: Electronic measurement provider Keysight (NYSE:KEYS) reported Q3 CY2024 results beating Wall Street’s revenue expectations, but sales fell by 1.8% year on year to $1.29 billion. On top of that, next quarter’s revenue guidance ($1.63 billion at the midpoint) was surprisingly good and 32% above what analysts were expecting. Its non-GAAP profit of $1.65 per share was 5% above analysts’ consensus estimates.
